The purpose of this study was to compare two different ways of helping people who have had childhood cancer, leukemia, tumors or similar illnesses learn health information and information about trying to quit smoking.

 All participants received materials in the mail about their health, survivorship, and smoking.

 Some participants were also invited to use a website.

 The goal of the study was to see which is a better way to get information about health issues, survivorship, and smoking.

